      • getValues

        public int getValues(Velocity target,
                     int tweenType,
                     float[] returnValues)

        Inherited method that takes an entity's velocity component, and returns the new values that were interpolated.

        Parameters:
        target - the starting velocity component.
        returnValues - An array of values that the interpolation will return.
        Returns:
        an integer value that represents the type of interpolation that was executed.

      • setValues

        public void setValues(Velocity target,
                      int tweenType,
                      float[] newValues)

        Function that sets the values inside of a given velocity component.

        Parameters:
        target - the current parallax component of the entity.
        tweenType - the type of tween to execute on the component.
        newValues - an array of values to be populated with new values.
